    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing... they're already grieving me, aren't they? they're grieving the version of me that was healthy and strong. every time they look at me now, they just see a problem they can't fix. it feels like a slow, painful goodbye every single day. if i could just... decide when that happens, instead of letting it drag on and drag them down with me, wouldn't that be more merciful? like, wouldn't a clean break be better for them than this long, slow decline?",
